      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAINT EUSTACE (3) has been going well. Finished second last start at Casterton after he saluted at Warrnambool the run prior. Racing well while gaining experience over the bigger fences this prep and this looks well within his grasp. NIGHTFALL (5) won two starts back in a maiden steeplechase at Te Aroha then was in the money again last time, beaten 23 lengths into third at Casterton at first start in Oz. Can only be better for that and any improvement makes him a major player here. RAISE THE NOTE (6) was unplaced two back at Warrnambool then again missed out at Hamilton last time. Capable of turning things around. BAZINI (1) was outclassed in the Thackeray but beat a handy one the start prior and only needs to repeat that to be a force here. MUNGERANNIE (7) did a reasonable job when he finished second in a flat race at Moe two runs back and while plain last start wasn't far off SAINT EUSTACE three starts back.",
